    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini nostri Iesu Christi Dei aeterni. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21">Berengarius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Si venerabilibus sanctarum Dei ecclesiarum
                        locis emolumentum regali munificentia quodlibet impendimus, et apud Deum
                        promereri veniam et regni nostri statum celitus roborari non ambigimus.
                        Idcirco omnium fidelium sanctae Dei Aecclesiae nostrorumque presentium
                        scilicet ac futurorum comperiat sollicitudo, quoniam pro mercede ac remedio
                        animae nostrae seu <rs key="#Intercessory">interventu</rs> nostrae
                        dilectissimae coniugis <persName key="#Intercessory #Queen"
                            ref="#people/155">Berthilae</persName>, quae regni nostri consors
                        dignoscitur, <rs key="#Intercessory">petitionem</rs> quoque ac precibus
                            <persName key="#Intercessory #Bishops"><name ref="Hildegarius"
                                >Hildegarii</name></persName> venerabilis <rs key="#Bishops"
                            >episcopi</rs> seu <persName key="#Intercessory #Palatine_count"
                            ref="#people/57">Sigefredi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Palatine_count">sacri palatii comitis</rs> nostrotum fidelium in
                            <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/108" key="#Mountains">sanctam Regiensem
                            ecclesiam</orgName> in honorem sanctae Dei genitricis Mariae atque beati
                        Christi confessoris Prosperi toto mentis affectu providentes eiusdem
                        ecclesiae neessitates vel depredationes atque incendia, quae a ferocissima
                        gente Hungrorum passa est, <placeName
                            key="#Confinia #Rivers #Mountains #Mansi #Landed_possessions #Forests #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Royal_slave"
                            ref="#places/497">montem Cervarium</placeName> simul cum <rs
                            key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >gaio</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Mansi #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >mansis</rs> inibi pertinentibus seu <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Royal_slave"
                            >familia utriusque sexus</rs> iuris palatii nostri, sicut subter per
                        denominatos terminos comprehensum videtur, Deo omnipotenti eiusque genitrici
                        semper virgini Mariae beatoque Prospero Christi confessori offerimus
                        perpetuoque habendum huius praecepti pagina stabilimus, sancientes pro
                        mercede et remedio animae nostrae prefatum montem Cervarium et gaio pariter,
                        ut dictum est, omnibusque mansis infra denominatos inferius terminos per
                        singula loca et vocabula constitutis seu <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Royal_slave"
                            >utriusque sexus familia</rs> cum <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >terris</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >silvis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >pratis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >montibus</rs>, planitiebus, <rs
                            key="#Rivers #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >rivis acquarumque decursibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >coltis et incoltis</rs>, omnia quicquid ad ipsum montem Cervarium vel
                        gaio pertinuisse conprobatur, <rs
                            key="#Confinia #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >cuius montis Cervarii eiusque rerum termini a <rs key="#Mountains"
                                >monte Deposci</rs> descendunt in <rs key="#Rivers">fluvium
                                Niteram</rs> que defluit in <rs key="#Rivers">flumen Inciam</rs>,
                            inde per Inciam sursum usque ad alpes</rs>; quae omnia et ex omnibus, ut
                        supra comprehensum est, ad partem sepe dicte aecclesiae hac nostre regali
                        auctoritate donamus ac cedimus, atque <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >de nostro iure in eius ius dominiumque transfundimus iure perpetuo
                            possidenda</rs>, absque alicuius inquietudine vel deminoratione. Si quis
                        vero temerarius huius nostri precepti institutionem violare temptaverit,
                        sciat se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">auri optimi libras centum</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Camera_regis">medietatem palatio nostro</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem sepe dictae
                            ecclesiae Regiensi</rs>. Et ut hoc verius credatur diligentiusque ab
                        omnibus observetur, manu propria subter roboravimus et anuli nostri
                        impressione subter insigniri iussimus. Signum domni (MF) Berengarii
                        gloriosissimi regis. <persName key="#Notary"><name ref="Fortunius"
                                >Fortunius</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/216">Ardigni</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovi et subscripsi. (SR) (SI D). Data pridie
                        non. Ian., anno incarnationis dominice DCCCCIIII, domni vero regni
                        Berengarii serenissimi regis XVII, indictione VIII. Actum <placeName
                            ref="#places/65">Papiae</placeName>. In Dei nomine feliciter, amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
